# Release Notes Format

When writing release notes for GRAIL, follow this format:

```
# GRAIL vX.X.X Release Notes

**Release Date:** Month DD, YYYY

### Highlights

- **Feature Name**: Brief description of the change and its impact.
- **Another Feature**: Keep each bullet to 1-2 sentences max.
```

Rules:
- Title: `# GRAIL vX.X.X Release Notes`
- Include release date in bold
- Use `### Highlights` section with bullet points
- Each bullet: **Bold title** followed by colon and description
- Keep descriptions concise (1-2 sentences)
- Focus on user-facing changes and impact
- Limit to 5-8 highlight items

